cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "run-farm: checkpointed campaign runs over a rented GPU spot fleet"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using these metadata."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: James P.
    family-names: Galasyn
  - given-names: Claude
    family-names: Théodore
repository-code: "https://github.com/JimGalasyn/run-farm"
url: "https://github.com/JimGalasyn/run-farm"
abstract: >-
  A physics-agnostic engine for running 10^4-10^6 registered, restartable
  simulation campaigns over a rented GPU spot fleet. It provides a config-hashed
  run registry with bit-identical restart from full-state checkpoints, streamed
  event records with triggered full-field capture, probe-or-bail admission
  control for flaky marketplace hosts, and leak-proof, teardown-verified cloud
  brokers for Vast.ai, RunPod, and Modal. An engine plugs in a single injected
  callable; nothing in the orchestration layer imports a model or a solver.
keywords:
